Introduction
Our Privacy Policy will help you understand what information we collect at Blood Donors, how we use it, and what choices you have. Blood Donors was built as a free app provided by OPVG and is intended for use as is. By choosing to use our Service, you agree to the collection and use of information as described in this policy. The personal information that we collect is used to provide and improve the Service. We will not use or share your information with anyone except as described in this Privacy Policy.

Terms used in this Privacy Policy have the same meanings as in our Terms and Conditions, which are accessible on our website, unless otherwise defined in this Privacy Policy.

Information Collection and Use
For a better experience while using our Service, we may require you to provide certain personally identifiable information, including but not limited to your name, email address, gender, location, and profile picture. This information will be retained by us and used as described in this privacy policy. The app may also use third-party services that collect information to identify you.

Cookies
Cookies are files with a small amount of data, often including an anonymous unique identifier. Cookies are sent to your browser from websites you visit and are stored on your device.

This app does not explicitly use cookies. However, it may employ third-party code and libraries that use cookies to collect information and improve their services. You have the option to accept or refuse cookies, and to be notified when a cookie is sent to your device. Please note that refusing cookies may limit your use of some parts of the Service.

Location Information
Some of our services may use location data transmitted from your mobile device. We only use this information within the necessary scope for the designated service, such as to match donors and recipients based on location.

Device Information
In some cases, we collect information from your device to provide a better service and prevent fraud. This information does not include details that identify you personally.

Service Providers
We may employ third-party companies and individuals for the following reasons:

To facilitate our Service
To provide the Service on our behalf
To perform Service-related tasks
To help us analyze how our Service is used
These third parties may have access to your personal information to perform these tasks on our behalf. However, they are obligated not to disclose or use the information for any other purpose.

Security
We value your trust in providing us with your personal information and strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect it. However, remember that no method of transmission over the Internet or method of electronic storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee its absolute security.

Childrenâ€™s Privacy
Our Service does not address anyone under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from children under 13. If we discover that a child under 13 has provided us with personal information, we will promptly delete this data from our servers. If you are a parent or guardian and you are aware that your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us to allow us to take the necessary actions.

Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy periodically. Therefore, we recommend reviewing this page for any changes. We will notify you of updates by posting the revised Privacy Policy on this page. Changes are effective immediately after they are posted on this page.

